J.C. Penney Names Apple’s Johnson as CEO

-- B y   B i l l   K o e n i g
-- 
2011-06-14T15:40:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/j-c-penney-names-apple-s-johnson-as-ceo.html
J. C. Penney Co. said it named  Ron
Johnson  as its next chief executive officer.  Johnson succeeds Myron Ullman, III in that post. Johnson
will assume the CEO job on Nov. 1, the company said. Johnson has
been senior vice president of retail at  Apple Inc. (AAPL)  the past 11
years.  J.C. Penney also said Johnson will make an investment of
$50 million in the company by purchasing warrants on 7.257
million shares of company stock. The warrants can’t be sold or
hedged for the first six years of their 7.5-year term, the
company said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Koenig at 
 wkoenig@bloomberg.net  